<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="421" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,152,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[952,1019,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">longi-</emphasis>
(= long) and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1303,1399,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">saccatus</emphasis>
(= saccus), referring to the very long saccus in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
